column_.text_:
Can't believe it. I thought if we beat Angra Mainyu, we'd be free to
go on our merry way.
No kidding. Why did Id have to go off and become Bahamut?
Right... In which case...

Hey, what're you thinking about, Rolan? Looks like you've got all
your gears whirring.

It's starting to come together now... Especially if she used a mind
sealer on him.

The mind sealer is what they used to rob Lyria of her free will...
What does it have to do with Bahamut?

Everything. Lilith and Bahamut, destruction and rebirth...
Everything is linked.
How about giving us the gist?

Essentially, it comes down to why Lilith failed to wake Angra
Mainyu fifteen years ago.

I heard the Sky Realm's Bahamut appeared after sensing an
overwhelming Astral presence. Perhaps that was more than
rumor.
You call that the gist? I'm even more confused!

Sorry. Fifteen years ago, Lilith summoned Angra Mainyu. At the
same time, Bahamut manifested to face her.

But this was not the same Bahamut you all know. Let us call it
Bahamut Versa.

It sensed the unfathomable power of Angra Mainyu—and 
consumed it.
Stopping Lilith in her tracks. But now...

Perhaps... to remove Bahamut from the picture. Lilith trapped the
primal inside Id, using the mind sealer.

Okay, but that doesn't explain why she suddenly freed Versa. Does
she want to wreck the skies or what?

She once told Id that she would destroy the world to bring about its
rebirth.

Versa is more than capable of forcing reincarnation upon the Sky
Realm.

In any case, we know one thing for sure: If we leave Versa to its
own devices, it will be the end of all life as we know it.
You've gotta be kidding. How are we gonna defeat a world crusher?

And what's gonna happen to Id? You aren't asking us to kill him,
are you?
Not gonna happen!
Not gonna happen!
Not gonna happen!
Thank you, . He doesn't deserve death.

Heh. I've still got a debt to settle with that punk. Can't let him off so
easily.
How do you know Id's still in there?
Even Bahamut's got nothing on Id.
Even Bahamut's got nothing on Id.
Even Bahamut's got nothing on Id.

Exactly. Guy with a stick that far up his butt? Even an apocalyptic
dragon couldn't push him down!

Even if we can't get through to him, he'll survive a beating. He
trounced us, right?

I've been around for a long time, but you skydwellers never cease
to surprise me.

I never would have dreamed that a single crew could save
Tempeal... or pacify Excavallion... or defeat Angra Mainyu.

But you've taught me that it's not longevity or physical strength
that's important... It's the power of your heart.

You have my complete faith. I believe that nothing in all the world
will keep you from saving your friend.
It's settled! We smack Versa like a piñata, till it coughs up Id!
Yeah!
Yeah!
All right... Let's go.
Come on. We got this!

This world is precious. I mean, even the god of destruction
can't bear to lose it.

This world is precious. I mean, even the god of destruction
can't bear to lose it.

Our bodies might be mortal, but our hearts are infinite.
Though he's in a dark place right now, I hope Id doesn't lose
sight of that.

Our bodies might be mortal, but our hearts are infinite.
Though he's in a dark place right now, I hope Id doesn't lose
sight of that.
But even if he does, I'll open his eyes again.
But even if he does, I'll open his eyes again.
I—this crew—will never abandon someone we care about.
I—this crew—will never abandon someone we care about.

The sunrise spills over the Grandcypher as we rush on the
winds, chasing the sorrowful cries of a faraway dragon...

The sunrise spills over the Grandcypher as we rush on the
winds, chasing the sorrowful cries of a faraway dragon...
Let me help you.
Me too!
Thanks for the support...
I won't waste it!
The spell is perfect... And yet...
It seems the binding... is only half effective...
... The rest is up to you.
You must... save Id...

Versa won't be able to stray far from the sigil while it's still in
effect.

I'll maintain the spell for as long as possible, but we're in a
race against time. Hold nothing back!

Okay, this is the last fight. You better fight 'til you drop or
Id's a goner!

I've trained endlessly so I can protect this crew. I swear on
my sword, you will not take Id or the skies from us!

So you're the apocalypse incarnate. Big whoop. Skydwellers
fly through death every day!
All right, Id. One magic cleansing coming right up!

Listen. I am this close to a fishing trip and a lemon iced tea.
This brawl's gonna go fast!

At the end of the day, even the god of destruction kneels to
the Rose Queen.

Fugee, Nicola, Geegee, Beppo, Momo. Can you handle one
more battle? We've got a friend in need!

I don't know if my fangs will be a match for the dragon of
destruction... But I won't abandon my comrade to you!

You guys don't need to be scared. I'm gonna take care of
everything!

Cast aside your fear... Be they infernal or divine, none can
withstand the ineluctable wreaths of my flame.

I've already felled dragons... But today, I shall add a god
to that list.

I swear, as Captain of the Lumiel Order, I shall not rest until
Id is safe once more!

Well, you can't reel up a catch any bigger than this. Best get
my fill while I can!
Pierce the skies, shatter the earth... and bring down a god.

I have envisioned many times over what my death match
with Bahamut would look like... And this was not it.

This is it. The battle to end all battles. Time to save the world,
Arvess!

I didn't come this far to die a meaningless death. Fight with
me, Grynoth. Today we rage!

As much as I'd love to do some data collection, guess my
biggest priority is not getting blown to smithereens.
You're going down.

Bahamut Versa represents both creation and destruction. Its
aubergine wings drive the evolution of all beings.

Life gives way to death, and death begets life... Our attempt
to intervene with this process may have far-reaching
consequences.

But I want to believe in the limitless potential of
skydwellers... I want to believe you can rewrite even
the laws of reality!

Id's hurting really bad... He's sad and empty... We haven't
known each other for too long, but I can feel it.

He wouldn't want things to end like this. We just have
to save him!

Who cares if you're stuck inside Bahamut? I'll bust you out
myself if I have to.

Id, you were betrayed by the woman who raised you and
made into a dragon's vessel for fifteen years... And yet you,
a mere mortal, survived.

If I should fail to rescue you, I don't think I shall ever forgive
myself for the rest of my long, long life.

In the past, I had merely existed... It wasn't until you
skydwellers let me into your hearts that I learned what it
was to live.

Unlike immortals, you are capable of change and growth...
All I want is to be a part of that—to help you build a glowing
future.

As an Astral, I am also to blame for the failures of my people.
And I swear to you now, I will set things right again!

I don't like to admit it, but gods are a little beyond our skill
level. We need more firepower!

I think you mean dragon power! Lyria, do you feel up to
summoning Bahamut?
Okay. Just give me some time!
No! It can't be!
That... is the light of the apocalypse. The fire of doomsday.

Its power is transcendent. If the attack lands, all the skies
will be obliterated!
Id, please... Stop this...
We know you don't want this, Id! So hurry and wake up!

You halted the charge! But it's already stored up considerable
energy...
Oh no... We're not going to make it!
Quit tryin' to fry us, dagnabbit!
Everyone! Gather around me!
Get to Lyria! Now!
I'll keep you all safe, I promise!
No... Nooo!
Please survive!
They're alive! Lyria, you did it...
Please, Bahamut...
Save us!
Time to turn the tables!
Id!
Not quite!
I'll hold Versa back!
Just worry about saving Id!
Graah... Groooar!

Unless my eyes deceive me... That's Id under all those scales,
isn't it?

He's been tainted by Versa's destructive urges... But it
seems his body and soul are still in one piece.

And that means there's still hope! If you can sever the
spiritual shackles that bind Id to Versa, he'll come back!

Id! Don't you remember? You made a promise! Is this your
idea of protecting Lyria?!

You finally crawled out from under Lilith's thumb! And now
you're gonna let yourself be crushed under Versa's?!
Not, your problem... Leave!

You can't push us away! Without us, you're pretty much the
awkwardest person I've ever met!
Heh. She's right, kid. Face it—you need us!
Run... away... Please... Ruuuun!

I thought you knew us better than that, Id. None of us would
ever abandon a friend!
Get a hold of yourself, Id!

You can't let the world end here. You haven't even had a
chance to live your own life yet!
Live... my own life...
I must see... my task through...
What in the...
No... Versa is trying to take full control of Id's body!
Well we're not gonna let that happen.
The end... is near...

Id's mind is growing more and more fractured! You need to
bring him back now!
Did we do it?
I can't believe they didn't make it...
N-no... The skies are...
Ahhh!
I will destroy... the skies...
I won't... let you!
He's starting to break free from Versa! Just a little more!
Hey, bud! Why don't we give him a wake-up call?
Hey, bud! Why don't we give him a wake-up call?
Got it!
Got it!
Id!
Id!
Id!
Id! Come back to us!
Ly... ria?
Versa still has a hold on Id. But now that he's human again,
You have one last chance to wrest him completely free!
I don't know... what to believe anymore...

You should at least believe in yourself, doofus! Think back to
when you were fighting to protect the skies!

Did that feel like a lie to you? No! Because that was what you
actually wanted!
What I... wanted?
Yes. Whenever you feel confused... Just follow your heart.

It might lead you to scary places... But at least you'll know
you're being true to yourself.
Id, you have to remember!
Id, you have to remember!

I want to be a defender... To all of you... To Lyria... To the
skies!

What's that giant rift? Ah! It must be the gate to Versa's
home dimension.

Versa is now a manifestation of sheer power with no vessel
to contain it. It won't be able to linger in this world much
longer.
If you can just weather these next attacks, the day is yours!
Right...
If I can get rid of Versa, I might finally find closure...

All right, Versa. Let's see how you like a taste of your own
medicine. I'll use your powers against you...
Even though there's so much at stake, I feel strangely calm...

We're veteran skyfarers! This ain't our first apocalyptic
rodeo, and it won't be our last!

If I had a rupie for every immortal butt we kicked, I could
probably buy my own island by now.

I don't mean to get mushy, but... I'm really proud to be a part
of this crew.

I feel the same way. I won't let anything happen to you or our
world.
Our journey can't end here!

It's not gonna. We're gonna kick some dragon tail and go on
sailing to the end of the skies!

All right, Versa. Let's see how you like a taste of your own
medicine. I'll use your powers against you...
And save the world you want to destroy!
This can't be happening... We'd only just managed to save Id!
Please, stop... Stooop!
Lyria! !
Id? You...
The truth... hurts.
All that I've suppressed... in the back of my mind...
Damn it.
I should've realized it sooner.
No use running... anymore...
I am who I am!
Primeval dragon...
Child of darkness and flames...
Thy name is...
Bahamut!
Kick its butt!

Amazing... Absolutely amazing. You've suppressed Versa's
core and driven it back to its home dimension!
Is everyone... safe now?
Thanks for everything...
Hehe. You can buy me some apples on the way back.
...! We're still not done!
Leave this to me.
, wait! Where do you think you're going?!
Forgive me.
Kids these days... You two are totally nuts.
Don't worry... I'll be back soon.
Oh, good! I was so worried!
What's the big idea!
What's the big idea!
Don't you ever do that again!
How do you think we'd feel if ya never came back, huh?
I mean if wasn't for Fix It Dude, you'd be...
That's Rolan to you, Vyrn.
You okay, man? Where are you?
Hm... Good question. Someplace far away?
Hey, this ain't the time for jokes.
He and Bahamut are trapped on another plane.
Think of it as a sliver between dimensions.
Still, considering his transceiver seems to be working...
For now. Sadly I think my time's almost up.
The line's going to get cut earlier than I'd hoped.

Thought I'd still be able to open a gate from here.
Guess not.
Isn't there anything we can do?
Sure! Just stay calm! No need to worry about little old me.
I'm Mr. Fix It, remember?
There's no jam I can't get myself out of, y'know!
I'll make it.
Rolan...
Oh, one last thing. So until I get back...

It'd take a load off my mind if you could check in on the
people of Folca.

I don't want them losing sleep over me being stuck in this,
uh, tricky situation.
Just... tell them... do... kay...
Don't go, Fix It Dude!
Folca...

That's where we bumped into Rolan when we first arrived in
the Zegagrande Skydom.
I have to atone.
For Mother's crimes. And mine.
C'mon, no need to beat yourself up, kid.
That's right. We couldn't have resolved this without you.
Id, you saved all of us.
In my opinion...

Deep down you knew you were fighting to help the skies. I'm
sure of it.
So it's not really about atonement.
I know it's been tough recently...
But I think the Sky Realm is better than it was before!
Let's visit Folca. Couldn't hurt.

No, wait. Don't let me off so easy. You all deserve an
apology—
C'mon...
Cut the formality. We already said it was fine, right?
You're one of us now, got me?
Woo-hoo! Who's ready to set sail?
Setting course for Ainsteddo Archipelago.
Full speed ahead to beautiful Folca!
Of course, I'll never forget everything you've done, .
Never ever.
Never ever.

And when we find Rolan, we'll give him the thanks he
deserves.

We've met so many people in the Zegagrande Skydom. New
friends. New allies.

We saw a man torn in two by family and betrayal. We were
saved by an immortal who found beauty in our changing
world.

Through loss and adversity, our resolve brought Lyria and I
closer than ever before.
Yet this story is far from over.

A good friend is still out there, waiting for us to come get
him.
And as for our journey? There's still much to see.

To the ends of the skies where the stars reside. Someday we
will reach Estalucia.
